Kimchi (Source Code)

1.  Download & Extract

-   Download kimchi-.zip
-   Extract to: Folder

2.  Install Required Software

Node.js - Verify: node -v npm -v - Used: Node.js v24.16.0 npm 11.13.0

Bun - Verify: bun –version - Used: 1.3.14

Go - Install Go and verify: go version - Used: go1.26.4 windows/amd64

pnpm - Install: npm install -g pnpm - Verify: pnpm -v

3.  Install Project Dependencies

From project root: npm install

4.  Verify Project Builds

npm run build

Should complete without errors.

5.  Run First-Time Setup

Instead of: npm run dev

(use of make fails on Windows)

Run: bun run –preload ./src/set-package-dir.ts src/entry.ts

Complete setup wizard.

Kimchi creates: C:-Admin.config

and downloads: fd.exe rg.exe

6.  Build proxy-helper.exe Manually

Go to: cd tools-helper

Build: go build -ldflags=“-s -w” -o bin/proxy-helper.exe .

Verify: tools-helper-helper.exe

exists.

7.  Patch scripts/build-binary.js

Original:
if (!isCI) {
	run("build proxy-helper", "make -C tools/proxy-helper build")
}

Replace with: 
if (!isCI) {
    if (platform() === "win32") {
        console.log("Using existing proxy-helper.exe")
    } else {
        run("build proxy-helper", "make -C tools/proxy-helper build")
    }
}

8.  Patch package.json

Original: "clean": "rm -rf dist"

Replace with:
"clean": "node -e \"require('fs').rmSync('dist',{recursive:true,force:true})\"",

9.  Build Windows Binary

npm run build:binary

Build reaches: → compile compile dist/bin/kimchi.exe

and creates: dist.exe

10. Resource Copy Error (Safe to Ignore)

Build later fails because: tools/proxy-helper/bin/proxy-helper

is expected on Linux/macOS, but Windows creates: proxy-helper.exe

Error: copy resources failed ENOENT proxy-helper

However: dist.exe

is already successfully generated kimchi.exe.

Final Result

The EXE was built successfully despite the final resource-copy step
failing.
